cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about designing a locomotion gait for a snake-like robot. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses a model-free reinforcement learning algorithm to train the controller. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses proximal policy optimization (PPO) algorithm for training the controller. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with the control task of a highly redundant degree of freedom system. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely as the paper does not explicitly mention any computer vision or image processing techniques.
